Best company pie ever. Make this when everyone else is making the typical apple pie. More sophisticated and easier [only has one crust to work with]. I have been making this since 1992. Must double the topping and make sure that you use exactly the amount of apples called for in the recipe- by weight. Normally I am not so fussy about "weighing" fruit for fillings and would just "guesstimate". You will have either too much custard [soggy] or not enough [dry and curdled]so, weigh the apples. Use an apple suited for pies such as spies [best for pies]. I sometimes make this in a 9" tart pan with a loose removable bottom and use pate brisee for crust. [very crisp but sturdy enough to take out of the tart pan]

