Rating: 0
I've been making a Silver Palate version of this dish for years and years, and this one is just as good. On top of it, the crust for this one is MUCH easier to make!!! I would also note that the first time piecooker should be sure to keep all the crust indgredients CHILLED--like after you cut up the shortening and butter, roll it in flour, and pop it in the fridge or freezer--if it gets to warm, its hard to handle. Also, I used a food but just pulse the machine so that the heat from the engine in the processor does not heat up the pie crust that you want to stay cool. I doubled the topping also, and used 5 small apples that weighed exactly 51/4lbs., which is why I think some people did not have enough custard if they used large apples! Overall, FAB-U-LOUS!!!!!! I couldn't stop eating the apples raw in the custard!

